"title": "5517: seafaring",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5517",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Ideas and images drawn from seafaring are used in Scripture to illustrate important aspects of the Christian life. Although Israel was not a seafaring nation, ships and sailing played a part in her history, as they did in the spreading of the gospel in the NT.</p>\n<h2>Israel's harbours</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:13\">GEN 49:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:17\">JDG 5:17</a></p>\n<h2>The art of shipbuilding</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:3-Ezek27:9\">EZK 27:3–27:9</a></p>\n<h2>Ships used for various purposes</h2>\n<h3>Deliverance from danger: Noah's ark</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:1-Gen9:17\">GEN 6:1–9:17</a></p>\n<h3>Trade</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:27-1Kgs9:28\">1KI 9:27–9:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:18\">2CH 8:18</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:25\">EZK 27:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:11\">1KI 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:22\">1KI 10:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:21\">2CH 9:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:48-1Kgs22:49\">1KI 22:48–22:49</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:35-2Chr20:37\">2CH 20:35–20:37</a></p>\n<h3>Slavery</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:68\">DEU 28:68</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:11-Rev18:13\">REV 18:11–18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Invasion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:24\">NUM 24:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:9\">EZK 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:30\">DAN 11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:40\">DAN 11:40</a></p>\n<h3>To carry refugees</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:9\">ISA 60:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>To carry passengers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:3\">JON 1:3</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:1\">MAT 9:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:4\">ACT 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:13\">MAT 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:39\">MAT 15:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:9\">MRK 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:13\">ACT 13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:26\">ACT 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:39\">ACT 15:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:11\">ACT 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:18\">ACT 18:18</a> <em>Paul sails for Syria with Aquila and Priscilla</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:21\">ACT 18:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:3\">ACT 20:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:6\">ACT 20:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:13-Acts20:16\">ACT 20:13–20:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:1-Acts21:3\">ACT 21:1–21:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:6-Acts21:7\">ACT 21:6–21:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:1-Acts27:8\">ACT 27:1–27:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:11-Acts28:13\">ACT 28:11–28:13</a></p>\n<h2>Seafarers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:23-Ps107:30\">PSA 107:23–107:30</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:25\">2CO 11:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:48\">1KI 22:48</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:37\">2CH 20:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:3-Jonah1:15\">JON 1:3–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:23-Matt8:27\">MAT 8:23–8:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:35-Mark4:41\">MRK 4:35–4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:22-Luke8:26\">LUK 8:22–8:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:22-Matt14:33\">MAT 14:22–14:33</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:45-Mark6:53\">MRK 6:45–6:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:16-John6:21\">JHN 6:16–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:9-Acts27:44\">ACT 27:9–27:44</a></p>\n<h2>Judgment on seafarers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:1\">ISA 23:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:16\">ISA 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:14\">ISA 23:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:21-Isa33:23\">ISA 33:21–33:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:14\">ISA 43:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:26-Ezek27:36\">EZK 27:26–27:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:17-Rev18:19\">REV 18:17–18:19</a></p>\n<h2>Metaphorical references to ships and seafaring</h2>\n<h3>Spiritual immaturity as a ship tossed at sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:14\">EPH 4:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Abandoning sound teaching as shipwreck</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:19\">1TI 1:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Faith as an anchor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:19\">HEB 6:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Other seafaring analogies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:4-Jas3:5\">JAS 3:4–3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:7\">PSA 48:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:14\">PRO 31:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:6\">JAS 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Noah's ark as a symbol of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:20\">1PE 3:20</a></p>",
